### Price Elasticity of Demand (PED) Breakdown
---
**Perfectly Inelastic (=0)**: Demand does not change at all with price

---
**Inelastic (0<PED<1)**: Demand changes less than price; customers are not very sensitive to price

---
**Unit Elastic (=1)**: Demand changes proportionally with price

---
**Elastic  (1<PED<∞)**: Demand changes more than price; customers are price-sensitive

---
**Perfectly Elastic (= ∞)**: Even tiny price changes cause demand to drop to zero
